Two women have sustained serious to moderate injuries after a motor vehicle in which they were travelling crashed into a wall at the underground parking at Rosebank Mall in Johannesburg on Monday. According to Netcare 911 reports, both women were occupants of the vehicle, but the cause the accident is unknown. Netcare911 paramedics worked alongside paramedics from other emergency services on scene. While assessing the injured, it was found that the elderly woman was in a serious but stable condition, and the other woman sustained moderate injuries, Netcare 911 said. They were both stabilised on scene and transported to a nearby hospital for further medical care. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.